{"sequence":17,"timestamp":"2026-04-17T05:51:03.948755610Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-52755d8e","body":"finding_summary: `project create --from-requirements` does not emit the new deprecation notice. In `src/cli/project.rs:185-189`, the `Create` branch bypasses `handle_create(...)` and jumps straight to `handle_create_from_requirements(run_id)` when `--from-requirements` is present, and `src/cli/project.rs:267-316` never calls `print_deprecation_notice(...)`. That leaves one of the primary legacy `project create` entry points without the promised stderr warning, which violates the bead scope and acceptance criteria. The existing regression coverage for this path in `tests/cli.rs:6940-7009` only asserts success/stdout behavior, so the gap is currently untested. remediation_hint: emit the notice before branching on `from_requirements` or at the top of `handle_create_from_requirements`, and extend one of the `project_create_from_requirements_*` tests to assert the warning appears on stderr.","dedup_key":"e844d5b9eed431c0756f53313b3077a7bb1a512eb2d13a49afeca077dccc448e","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260417052928","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":18,"timestamp":"2026-04-17T05:51:03.957153859Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-eb904524","body":"Coverage gap: `handle_create_from_requirements` in src/cli/project.rs (line 267) is dispatched from `ProjectSubcommand::Create` when `--from-requirements` is set (src/cli/project.rs:185-191), but unlike the sibling `handle_create` (line 201) it does not call `print_deprecation_notice`. Result: `ralph-burning project create --from-requirements <run-id>` produces no deprecation warning even though it's a project-surface entry point the user is supposed to migrate away from. The surrounding `handle_create` path does warn, so a user only sees a deprecation notice for some invocations of `project create`, which is inconsistent.\n\nRemediation: add `print_deprecation_notice(\"create --from-requirements\", \"<recommended replacement>\")` at the top of `handle_create_from_requirements`. If no clear replacement exists today (since `milestone create --from-requirements` does not exist), the spec permits a softer phrasing (e.g., \"This command surface is deprecated and may move to `milestone` in a future release\"). Either approach resolves the inconsistency so every `project create ...` invocation gets the same deprecation signal.","dedup_key":"9a328ed6ac85162e4f1118b8c0a7dfde926d7df5814fe840ad3aa927251b37d9","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-7-max","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260417052928","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
