{"sequence":35,"timestamp":"2026-04-17T06:14:05.565037537Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-3ecddec9","body":"finding_summary: The new deprecation notice for `project select` points users at a replacement that is not behaviorally equivalent for bead-backed projects. `project select` still synchronizes the active milestone (`src/cli/project.rs:686-693`), but `task select` only updates the active project pointer (`src/cli/task.rs:96-100`). Milestone commands resolve the active milestone from the saved milestone pointer before falling back to the active project (`src/cli/milestone.rs:543-560`), so following the advertised replacement can leave the workspace on the wrong milestone and send later `milestone next` / `milestone run` / `milestone status` commands to the previously active milestone.\naffected_files: src/cli/project.rs, src/cli/task.rs\nremediation_hint: Make `task select` reuse the same selection helper as `project select`, including `sync_active_milestone_from_project_record`, and add a bead-backed integration test that asserts `task select` updates the active milestone as well as the active project.","dedup_key":"8a3f7b8765cb602b2d24e7182ac6ab60fb7597d032dba4ccec53f7f5ef426410","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260417052928","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
